                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WALTER MEARS</hi> (19)</persName>
                  <rs id="t18650410-491-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18650410-491-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="violentTheft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18650410-491-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="robbery"></interp>, Robbery on <persName id="t18650410-name-667" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-667" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-667" type="surname" value="VICKRESS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-667" type="given" value="REBECCA"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18650410-491-offence-1 t18650410-name-667"></join>Rebecca Vickress</persName>, and stealing from her person, 1 pencil-case, 1 purse, 1 piece of paper, and 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 16<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. her goods.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. WOOD</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650410-name-668" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-668" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-668" type="surname" value="VICKRESS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-668" type="given" value="REBECCA"></interp>REBECCA VICKRESS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a widow, living at Billinghurst, in Essex—on 27th March, between 4 and half-past, I was coming out of a shop in the Westminster-road—I was not quite certain I had all the articles I had bought; I turned round to put my purse in my pocket, when a lad came up, gave me a blow in the chest, and snatched my purse away—there were three of them together—I have no means of identifying the prisoners—I was so surprised and frightened—I had between 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. and 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. in money, a gold pencil-case, and a bank-stock receipt for 400<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. in my purse—the purse has not been seen since—I ran after the man to Mason-street—a boy named Piper said the man had run down Mason-street—I called "Stop thief! "</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650410-name-669" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-669" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-669" type="surname" value="PIPER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-669" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL PIPER</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at 121, Westminster-bridge Read, and am engaged by Mr. Rogers, a bootmaker—on the afternoon of 27th March, I saw, about half-past 4, the last witness in the Westminster-bridge-road—I was I standing in a doorway—I heard a cry of "Stop thief! "and saw Mears running as hard as he could run—I knew him previously by sight—he turned up Mason-street—he had something small in his hand, but I could not see what it was; his hand was closed—he turned round Mason-street,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="186504100203"></xptr>
               <p>and ran up Blythe-terrace, and I loot sight of him—I then came down Mason-street, and saw Mrs. Vickreas speaking to a constable—I then went indoors.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did Mears run as fast as he could? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes; I could not catch him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650410-name-670" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-670" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-670" type="surname" value="CARROLL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-670" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN CARROLL</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at 77, Carlisle-street—on 27th March, about half-past 4, I saw the two prisoners in the Westminster-bridge-road running away, and heard the prosecutrix crying "Stop thief!"—I had known the prisoners a long time before—I afterwards saw the lady speaking to a con<lb></lb>stable, and I gave him information of what I had seen—-Donovan was running I about half a yard ahead of the other, and the lady was about half a dozen yards behind them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">DONOVAN</hi>. Why didn't you give me in charge, you saw me on the Friday following. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. I did not know whether to give him in charge or not; there was no policeman near at the time.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. WOOD</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you any doubt whatever about these being the two men the lady was following? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Oh, no; I am sure they are right.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650410-name-671" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-671" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-671" type="surname" value="HARDINGHAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-671" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT HARDINGHAM</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Policeman, L</hi> 163.) I took the twoprisoners into custody on 2d April—I took Mears first on 28th March; the last witness had not seen the prisoners then.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650410-name-672" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-672" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-672" type="surname" value="WINTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-672" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN WINTER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Policeman, L</hi> 88). I saw the prisoners together on the Saturday night previous to the robbery, about 12 as near as possible—I have also seen them together on several other occasions.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Mean' Defence.</hi> Is it possible for a man to go and steal a woman's purse at that time of the day, and run that distance without being stopped. I am innocent of this. I have been in trouble before, and if there is anything done of this kind the police take me on suspicion, whether innocent or not.</p>
               <p>
